article_title: Residents go door to door to round up support for Clinton

article_metadata.description: DOVER — Democrats were out across the state, rallying people to get out and canvass neighborhoods in support of Hillary Clinton's bid to win her party's nomination in her bid to be elected president in 2016.With the February primary coming up fast, Clinton supporters have declared this to be their week of action and so they are sending residents door to door lobbying for votes. Julie McLean, press secretary for the campaign, said that by the end of the week, they will done more than 200
article_metadata.author: Karen Dandurant news@fosters.com
